#: src/mathlib.c:788
msgid "Mathlib Benchmark Help"
msgstr "Mathlib-maatstaafhulp"

#: src/mathlib.c:790
msgid ""
"Jobs are forked and run in parallel by xnec2c, whereas threads are used by "
"the mathlib implementation to parallelize the linear algebra calculation of "
"one job.  For parallel algorithms you can reduce the number of threads in "
"use by the algorithm with the following environment variables:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS thread limit\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP thread limit\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL thread limit\n"
"\n"
"Each benchmark specifies a complexity to indicate approximately how long it "
"will take to run.  For example, O(N) means the time will scale with N and "
"O(N*J) means it will scale with N*J:\n"
"  * N is the number of mathlibs selected here:\n"
"      File->Mathlib Benchmarks->Selected Mathlibs\n"
"  * J is the number of jobs specified on the command line with -j (eg, -j "
"8)\n"
"\n"
"Higher complexity options run more benchmarks to provide additional "
"information about how you might optimize your xnec2c runtime.  The benchmark "
"menu options are as follows:  \n"
"\n"
"* Parallel (-j N): O(N/J) time: Benchmark each mathlib in parallel with the "
"number of jobs specified on the command line with -j.\n"
"\n"
"* Single Job (-j 1): O(N) time: Benchmark each mathlib with a single job "
"even if -j was specified on the command line. This is useful to find the "
"fastest interactive mathlib that is used when the frequency is changed in "
"the UI by changing a Frequency MHz +/- widget or (right-)clicking on the "
"frequency plot\n"
"\n"
"* Iterate -j N/=2: O(N*log2(J)) time: Benchmark each mathlib in parallel "
"initially with the number of jobs specified on the command line with -j, and "
"then reduce the number jobs by half for each subsequent iteration until only "
"one job remains.  This is useful to find a balance between the number of "
"parallel jobs specified by -j and the number of threads used by the linear "
"algebra library as modified by the environment variables listed above.\n"
"\n"
"* Iterate -j N-=2: O(N*J) time: Same as -j N/=2 above, but instead decrement "
"the number of jobs by 1.  This takes the longest to run.\n"
msgstr ""
"Take en drade word deur xnec2c gevurk en parallel uitgevoer, terwyl drade "
"deur die mathlib-implementering gebruik word om die lineêre algebra-"
"berekening van een taak te paralleliseer. Vir parallelle algoritmes kan jy "
"die aantal drade wat deur die algoritme gebruik word, verminder met die "
"volgende omgewingsveranderlikes:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS-draadlimiet\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP-draadlimiet\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL-draadlimiet\n"
"\n"
"Elke maatstaf spesifiseer 'n kompleksiteit om aan te dui hoe lank dit "
"ongeveer sal neem om te voltooi. Byvoorbeeld, O(N) beteken die tyd sal skaal "
"met N en O(N*J) beteken dit sal skaal met N*J:\n"
"  * N is die aantal mathlibs hier gekies:\n"
"      Lêer->Mathlib-maatstawwe->Gekose Mathlibs\n"
"  * J is die aantal take gespesifiseer op die opdragreël met -j (bv. -j 8)\n"
"\n"
"Hoër kompleksiteitsopsies voer meer maatstawwe uit om addisionele inligting "
"te verskaf oor hoe jy jou xnec2c-looptyd kan optimaliseer. Die maatstaf-"
"kieslysopsies is soos volg:  \n"
"\n"
"* Parallel (-j N): O(N/J) tyd: Maatstaf elke mathlib parallel met die aantal "
"take gespesifiseer op die opdragreël met -j.\n"
"\n"
"* Enkele Taak (-j 1): O(N) tyd: Maatstaf elke mathlib met 'n enkele taak "
"selfs al is -j op die opdragreël gespesifiseer. Dit is nuttig om die "
"vinnigste interaktiewe mathlib te vind wat gebruik word wanneer die "
"frekwensie in die UI verander word deur 'n Frekwensie MHz +/- kontrole te "
"verander of (regs-)klik op die frekwensiegrafiek\n"
"\n"
"* Itereer -j N/=2: O(N*log2(J)) tyd: Maatstaf elke mathlib parallel "
"aanvanklik met die aantal take gespesifiseer op die opdragreël met -j, en "
"verminder dan die aantal take met die helfte vir elke daaropvolgende "
"iterasie totdat slegs een taak oorbly. Dit is nuttig om 'n balans te vind "
"tussen die aantal parallelle take gespesifiseer deur -j en die aantal drade "
"wat deur die lineêre algebra-biblioteek gebruik word soos gewysig deur die "
"omgewingsveranderlikes hierbo gelys.\n"
"\n"
"* Itereer -j N-=2: O(N*J) tyd: Dieselfde as -j N/=2 hierbo, maar verminder "
"eerder die aantal take met 1. Dit neem die langste om te voltooi.\n"

