msgstr "Maatstawwe is gedeaktiveer terwyl optimalisering aktief is."

#: src/mathlib.c:847
msgid "You must load a NEC2 input file before running benchmarks."
msgstr "Jy moet 'n NEC2-invoerlêer laai voordat maatstawwe uitgevoer word."

#: src/mathlib.c:853
msgid ""
"Choosing a benchmark other than \"Single Job\" has no effect unless -j is "
"specified on the command line."
msgstr ""
"Die keuse van 'n maatstaf anders as \"Enkele Taak\" het geen effek tensy -j "
"op die opdragreël gespesifiseer word nie."

#: src/mathlib.c:870
msgid "You must select at least one math library to benchmark"
msgstr "Jy moet ten minste een wiskundebiblioteek kies om te toets"

#: src/mathlib.c:875
#, c-format
msgid ""
"This will run a frequency loop benchmark for each detected linear algebra "
"library and then provide a summary.  It may take some time to complete "
"depending on how big and how many frequencies your NEC2 will use. Detailed "
"timing will be provided in the terminal.\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"* Only one Intel MKL library can be tested without restarting xnec2c, so "
"select which one you wish to benchmark before proceeding or it will choose "
"the first in the list and skip the rest.\n"
"\n"
"* Thread congestion will occur for multi-threaded libraries when using the -"
"j N option if there are not enough CPUs available to accommodate the forked "
"processes in combination with library threads.  Consider reducing the value "
"of -j N for benchmarking to find what library works best with a mix of "
"forking and threading; you can use `top` to monitor your CPU usageand if it "
"reaches 0%% idle then you might consider reducing -j N.\n"
"\n"
"You may wish to experiment setting these environment variables:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS thread limit\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP thread limit\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL thread limit\n"
"\n"
"Click OK to proceed, this dialog will close when complete."
msgstr ""
"Dit sal 'n frekwensielus-maatstaf uitvoer vir elke opgespeurde lineêre "
"algebra-biblioteek en dan 'n opsomming verskaf. Dit kan 'n rukkie neem om te "
"voltooi afhangende van hoe groot en hoeveel frekwensies jou NEC2 sal "
"gebruik. Gedetailleerde tydsberekening sal in die terminaal verskaf word.\n"
"\n"
"Notas:\n"
"* Slegs een Intel MKL-biblioteek kan getoets word sonder om xnec2c te "
"herbegin, so kies watter een jy wil toets voordat jy voortgaan, anders sal "
"dit die eerste in die lys kies en die res oorslaan.\n"
"\n"
"* Draadopeenhoping sal voorkom vir multi-draad-biblioteke wanneer die -j N "
"opsie gebruik word as daar nie genoeg SVE's beskikbaar is om die gevurkte "
"prosesse in kombinasie met biblioteekdrade te akkommodeer nie. Oorweeg om "
"die waarde van -j N te verminder vir maatstawwe om te vind watter biblioteek "
"die beste werk met 'n mengsel van vurking en drade; jy kan `top` gebruik om "
"jou SVE-gebruik te monitor en as dit 0%% inaktief bereik, oorweeg dan om -j "
"N te verminder.\n"
"\n"
"Jy mag wil eksperimenteer deur hierdie omgewingsveranderlikes te stel:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS-draadlimiet\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP-draadlimiet\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL-draadlimiet\n"
"\n"
"Klik OK om voort te gaan, hierdie dialoog sal sluit wanneer voltooi."

